To create a new branch in Git, follow these steps:

Open your terminal or command prompt.

Navigate to your repository:

bash
Copy code
cd path/to/your/repo
Create a new branch:

bash
Copy code
git checkout -b new-branch-name
Replace new-branch-name with the name you want for your branch.

Verify the branch has been created:

bash
Copy code
git branch
This will list all branches, and your new branch should be highlighted.

Push the new branch to the remote repository (if needed):

bash
Copy code
git push origin new-branch-name
That's it! You've successfully created a new branch in Git.



